external_knowledge:
- "rivers of power" metaphorically refers to product lines with significant motor wattage;
- "still flowing" indicates the product is currently active (is_active = 1);
- "carry a current stronger than 2000 watts" refers to products with motor wattage greater than 2000 (motor_wattage > 2000);
- "vast plains of cooking" metaphorically refers to the category 'Pans'.

- "user satisfaction levels" refers to the average rating given by users; 
- "products that got some feedback" means products with at least one rating entry;
- "those who are still part of the community" refers to active users (is_active = 1).

- "sailed into the stormy seas of scarcity" refers to products that are out of stock;
- "set sail" metaphorically represents the launch of the product;
- "beyond the horizon" is used to indicate that the product is out of stock and not within the reach of immediate supply.

- "silent whispers" metaphorically refers to products that have not yet been announced or launched, hence they are silent in the market;
- "waiting in the wings" metaphorically means these products are prepared but not yet released to the public;
- The realm of hand mixers refers to the category of products known as "Hand Mixers".

sql:
SELECT f.product_id, f.feedback_text
FROM feedback f
INNER JOIN sales s ON f.product_id = s.product_id;
